4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, a
6 resident is protected from the unreasonable search and
7 seizure of his or her person, house, papers, and
8 possessions.
9 Also under the Constitution of Alabama of 2022
10 and existing case law and statutory law, this
11 protection has been construed to require a warrant
12 issued only upon a showing of probable cause to search
13 or seize any of these protected items, subject to
14 several established exceptions.
15 Also under existing case law and statutory law,
16 real property that is not included within one's house,
17 known as open fields, does not enjoy this protection
18 from unreasonable search and seizure.
19 This bill would require a government agent to
20 have a warrant to enter any private real property or
21 seize personal property on private real property,
22 subject to several specified exceptions.
23 This bill would require a government agent
24 entering private real property to take certain actions.
25 This bill would also provide for searches and
26 seizures conducted in violation of this bill.
